<br>
Also the minimum dly is less than 10.  How do you know? Get a moss covered twig.  Test it with and without haste.  Should be fairly clear that the twig which starts out 3 dmg 10 dly, hits considerably faster with haste meaning its hitting faster than its base 10 dly.  I would imagine the minimum dly is actually 1. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unortherner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/26/02 4:07:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22979.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/sjgardner/Images/celeris2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Nerf?</span><hr size=1> There is no such thing as minimum delay.  If you insist on looking at haste as delay reduction you can compute a new delay like this:<br>
<br>
new delay = old delay / (1+ total haste percentage)<br>
<br>
e.g.<br>
<br>
12.255 = 25 / (1+ (.4 + .64))  {for ragebringer with AQ}<br>
<br>
Note that this ignores any haste cap for the sake of illustration. <p><center><b><font color=RED><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78504>Celeris Tujimson</a><br>Blackguard of The Nameless<br>
